Package station

Class ParkingSlot

  • java.lang.Object
    • station.ParkingSlot
  • public class ParkingSlot
extends java.lang.Object
    Class representing station parking slot. It is the end point responsible for releasing and receiving bikes. For this, it uses methods receiveBike and releaseBike

      • receiveBike

        public void receiveBike​(Bike bike,
                        java.time.LocalDateTime time)
                 throws UnavailableBikeException,
                        UnavailableSlotException
        Method for receiving bike from user at a given time. This method should be called by the user when returning the bike. It will automatically call other functions for charging adequate payment and give time credit, and also updates VelibSystem statistics
        Parameters:
        bike - Bike being returned by the user. It must be given as a usr.getBike(), otherwise it will raise an exception
        time - Time of bike return. Must be a java.time.LocalDateTime value
        Throws:
        UnavailableBikeException - Exception thrown when the bike being returned is not registered under any user and is thus in fact unavailable
        UnavailableSlotException - Exception thrown when slot is not free. Should not be thrown here in normal usage. Was added for tests before implementation of a few classes

      • releaseBike

        public void releaseBike​(User usr,
                        java.time.LocalDateTime time)
                 throws UnavailableBikeException
        Method for releasing bike on command from terminal. It will attribute a payment regime to the user renting the bike, change slot status and user bike and update system statistics.
        Parameters:
        usr - User renting the bike. Should be informed by the station terminal after identification
        time - Time of bike rent. Should also be a java.time.LocalDateTime value
        Throws:
        UnavailableBikeException - Exception thrown when there is no bike in this slot or when it is out of order. Should not be thrown here in normal usage. Was added for tests before implementation of a few classes

      • setSlotOffline

        public void setSlotOffline​(java.time.LocalDateTime time)
                    throws IrregularOperationException
        Method for setting the slot as out of order. Implemented separately from setStatus because a few modifications for the calculation of statistics were needed
        Parameters:
        time - LocalDateTime of when the station was set off.
        Throws:
        IrregularOperationException - Exception thrown when the slot is already out of order before the command

      • setSlotOnline

        public void setSlotOnline​(java.time.LocalDateTime time)
                   throws IrregularOperationException
        Method for putting a slot back working. Implemented separately from setStatus because a few modifications for the calculation of statistics were needed
        Parameters:
        time - LocalDateTime of when the station was set on.
        Throws:
        IrregularOperationException - thrown when the slot is already functional before the command
